<subSubSection id="1F88107A1A325A235E5EA8481F3B76AB" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="8863CD2D4226F09DDF6238344871E634" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="581023D3AD8836A25BBDB30C1E98F11B" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">
Grateloup did not state on how many specimens his description was based; in 
<bibRefCitation id="1EAE62607C9B9428E6254E8FDF5D1750" author="Grateloup, JPS de" journalOrPublisher="Actes de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux" pageId="47" pageNumber="64" pagination="389 - 455" refId="B40" refString="Grateloup, JPS de, 1839b. Memoire descriptif sur plusieurs especes de coquilles nouvelles ou peu connus de mollusques exotiques vivants, terrestres, fluviatiles et marins. Actes de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux 11: 389 - 455" title="Memoire descriptif sur plusieurs especes de coquilles nouvelles ou peu connus de mollusques exotiques vivants, terrestres, fluviatiles et marins." volume="11" year="1839 b">Grateloup (1839b</bibRefCitation>
: 420) he gave as measurements &quot;Hauteur: 80 mill. - 
<normalizedToken id="EB73C9D7AE34A8758E33361F26D2A3E2" originalValue="Diamètre">Diametre</normalizedToken>
: 35 Mill.&quot; and said it was from &quot;Mon cabinet&quot;. As 
<bibRefCitation id="D27C05192F3FD966B63FB32EE377F7B8" author="Breure, ASH" journalOrPublisher="Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden" pageId="45" pageNumber="62" pagination="1 - 255" refId="B9" refString="Breure, ASH, 1978. Notes on and descriptions of Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Zoologische Verhandelingen Leiden 164: 1 - 255" title="Notes on and descriptions of Bulimulidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda)." volume="164" year="1978">Breure (1978)</bibRefCitation>
noted, this specimen &quot;From Grateloup Colln.&quot; came to the NHMUK collection via da Costa, who purchased the specimen from the dealers Sowerby and Fulton. 
<bibRefCitation id="5ED5386BED2D8F7F26AA6E8D9FA59865" author="Reeve, LA" journalOrPublisher="Reeve, Benham and Reeve, London" pageId="51" pageNumber="68" refId="B106" refString="Reeve, LA, 1848-1850. Conchologica iconica or illustrations of the shells of molluscous animals, 5. Bulimus. Reeve, Benham and Reeve, London" title="Conchologica iconica or illustrations of the shells of molluscous animals, 5. Bulimus" year="1848 - 1850">Reeve (1848 [1848-1850])</bibRefCitation>
evidently based his description on a different specimen, as he wrote &quot;The shell named 
<taxonomicName id="9FA2A2F7408B5355F23989C85FAD0199" authority="Scopoli, 1777" authorityName="Grateloup" authorityYear="1839" class="Gastropoda" family="Bulimulidae" genus="Bulimus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bulimus magnificus" order="Pulmonata" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="magnificus">
<emphasis id="27B9DD94A91095E8685CC7EBC043533F" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Bulimus magnificus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by M. Grateloup is, according to the specimen so marked in Mr. 
<normalizedToken id="E4ED36CA0748556AECFCF7E95661D84C" originalValue="Cuming’s">Cuming's</normalizedToken>
collection, a variety of 
<emphasis id="B815C9542C556B0933CE57606C83B19C" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Bulimus Taunaysii</emphasis>
[supposed by Reeve to be 
<normalizedToken id="15728329E5CFC6FC835B9299DE5FF119" originalValue="Férussac’s">Ferussac's</normalizedToken>
species] of a lighter brown colour&quot;. Despite the confusing localities (
<normalizedToken id="810187AADE29E7036F9270B6E34EB4F6" originalValue="“Brésil”">&quot;Bresil&quot;</normalizedToken>
seems to be added in a later hand), the status of this specimen is not disputed herein; the Peruvian locality, however, still needs confirmation. The current systematic position follows 
<bibRefCitation id="634AB6A8274C2CF0A8820AB16FEB4853" author="Simone, LRL" journalOrPublisher="EGB / Fapesp, Sao Paulo" pageId="52" pageNumber="69" refId="B121" refString="Simone, LRL, 2006. Land and freshwater molluscs of Brazil. EGB/Fapesp, Sao Paulo" title="Land and freshwater molluscs of Brazil." year="2006">Simone (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, who reported this species from the states of Rio de Janeiro and 
<normalizedToken id="78582D6EF6D09F4013ADC940CFA2FA76" originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A5546A58AB69C26AE720E6D48FC4EAC5" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" type="current systematic position">
